Mxolisi Mngadi, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; An inquest docket&nbsp;has been opened&nbsp;after a 24-year-old man was found dead inside a tractor on a construction site on the N3 interchange in Hammarsdale, KwaZulu-Natal police said on Tuesday.Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said the police&rsquo;s search and rescue unit found the man on Monday sitting in a tractor with a bowl of coals in front of him.Police suspect that the man died of carbon monoxide poisoning after making fire in a confined space."A post mortem will be conducted to determine the cause of death. Hammarsdale police are investigating the incident," said Zwane. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.